<h1 id="jodid25519">Jodid25519 <a href="https://travis-ci.org/meganz/jodid25519"><img alt="Build Status" src="https://secure.travis-ci.org/meganz/jodid25519.png" /></a></h1>

<p>Javascript implementation of the Curve25519 and Ed25519 elliptic cryptography functions by Daniel J. Bernstein.</p>

<p>For the API, please consult the generated documentation under doc/ (you can run <code class="prettyprint">make</code> to generate it).</p>

<p>To run the tests do the following on the console from the project&rsquo;s root directory:</p>

<p>$ npm install
    $ make test</p>

<h2 id="contributors">Contributors</h2>

<p>If you are one of the contributors and want to add yourself or change the information here, please do submit a pull request.   Contributors appear in no particular order.</p>

<h3 id="for-the-curve25519-submodule">For the Curve25519 submodule</h3>

<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/graydon">Graydon Hoare</a>: suggested clamping the private key by default for increased safety and uniformity with other implementations.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/liliakai">liliakai</a>: spotted an unused argument in some of the functions</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ryancdotorg">RyanC</a>: removed dependency of a function to the Javascript Math library</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/pohutukawa">Guy Kloss</a>: performance improvements through bit-shift operations, performance and conformance testing, documentation, compatibility with the npm package ecosystem, and more</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/rev22">Michele Bini</a>: originally wrote the Javascript implementation</li>
</ul>

